==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in 1792.
* From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|acclimater}}, from {{term|à}} + {{term|climat||climate}}  from {{etyl|la}} {{term|ad|lang=la}} + {{term|climat|lang=la}} , (English {{term|climate|lang=en}}) from {{etyl|grc}},, from {{proto|Indo-European}} – see {{term|climate|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈklaɪ.mət/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæk.lɪ.meɪt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-acclimate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|acclimat|ing}}

# {{transitive|chiefly|US}} To [[habituate]] to a [[climate]] not native; to [[acclimatize]].
# {{transitive}} To [[adjust]] to a new [[environment]]; not necessarily a wild, natural, earthy one.
# {{context|intransitive}} To become accustomed to a new climate or environment.

